00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,640
Yeah.

276
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,040
Oh.

277
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:08,480
Oh.

278
00:17:01,720 --> 00:17:05,960
Tell her to leave me alone.

279
00:17:06,080 --> 00:17:08,440
I do not have the strength.

280
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:15,040
Do you hear what I'm asking you?

281
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:23,600
I would if I wanted to.

282
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,000
But I don't.

283
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:34,400
What the hell are you doing?

284
00:17:34,520 --> 00:17:37,560
Shut up, darling, and move over.

285
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,200
You are insane.

286
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,960
I am calling the night nurse.

287
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:44,720
Right here at your service? Adam?

288
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,360
Ladies and gentlemen,

289
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:14,680
we bring now to the stage my daughter,

290
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:20,040
the amazing, the brain-bending,
Miss Ruthie.

291
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:21,280
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

292
00:18:29,680 --> 00:18:31,840
Isn't she so amazing?

293
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:32,880
You are my angel.

294
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,440
Do not be frightened.

295
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,280
You cannot see anything,
can you, Ruthie?

296
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:38,320
- No.
- No.

297
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:41,280
She says no.

298
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,960
She's looking askance at me,
my- my darling wife.

299
00:18:44,080 --> 00:18:46,520
Oh, I love to get a smile
out of my wife.

300
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:49,280
Give her a big hand.

301
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,400
What's down there?

302
00:18:50,520 --> 00:18:51,680
Ah, I love that.

303
00:18:51,800 --> 00:18:53,280
Ow.

304
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,400
My wife, Gretchen.

305
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:58,720
I pick up the first blade,
so absolute silence.

306
00:18:58,840 --> 00:18:59,760
Here we are.

307
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,240
Ruthie, don't.

308
00:19:06,360 --> 00:19:08,520
She will do anything to avoid this part.

309
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,280
You don't like this part,
but no brain bending.

310
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,360
That is-

311
00:19:43,280 --> 00:19:45,320
When you pulled up the thing
and you winked at the audience

312
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,320
and they went crazy,
you were killing me.

313
00:19:47,440 --> 00:19:48,360
That stays in the show.

314
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:49,440
Papa.

315
00:19:49,560 --> 00:19:50,720
You are a little genius, I think.

316
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:51,760
Papa, there's a man.

317
00:19:51,880 --> 00:19:53,760
Was that spontaneous,
or did you work it out before?

318
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:54,800
Tell me.

319
00:19:54,920 --> 00:19:56,840
- That's your bit.
- Adam, it's him.

320
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:02,040
Volk.

321
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,680
Well, Herr Stein.

322
00:20:07,800 --> 00:20:11,040
All performers must be members
of the Reichstheaterkammer.

323
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:13,320
You do not qualify.

324
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:15,000
No sense of humor at all.

325
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:16,720
Tell me this.

326
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:20,840
Did your men like that bit with the bear?

327
00:20:20,960 --> 00:20:22,800
Erschiessen.

328
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:36,840
You were warned, Adam.

329
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:48,880
I am not political.

330
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:51,320
Everyone loves the circus.

331
00:21:02,200 --> 00:21:03,160
Well, I have to admit,

332
00:21:03,280 --> 00:21:05,240
things have been less interesting around here.

333
00:21:05,360 --> 00:21:06,760
It seems incredible.

334
00:21:06,880 --> 00:21:09,120
A man who only yesterday spewed out

335
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,960
streams of blood from his toe.

336
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:15,000
Not to mention the pancreatic tumor
he sprouted in March.

337
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:18,400
And the heart attack last summer.

338
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:21,840
The man has actually spat out
part of a lung.

339
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:26,040
I mean, it's an amazing thing,
the self-destruction.

340
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,920
The amazing thing about Adam Stein

341
00:21:28,040 --> 00:21:30,400
isn't his control over his body.

342
00:21:30,520 --> 00:21:31,800
It's his power over you, Nathan.

343
00:21:31,920 --> 00:21:33,240
What?

344
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:35,520
And a few other staff members
I could name.

345
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:36,560
Relax, Uri.

346
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:37,920
Eat your foie gras.

347
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:40,240
- Adam.
- Look who's here.

348
00:21:40,360 --> 00:21:41,280
And, Wolfowitz, now look,

349
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:44,520
mein Gott im Himmel,
you look just awful.

350
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,840
It's just not- not good.

351
00:21:46,960 --> 00:21:50,000
Ah, Rachel, oh, you pumpkin.

352
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:51,360
Gorgeous, absolutely gorgeous.

353
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:53,800
And Zelda, dear, yeah,
you keep the sky from falling,

354
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,880
but- but sit.

355
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,640
Adam, Schwester's been dreaming again

356
00:21:56,760 --> 00:21:57,920
with her nonsense.

357
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,680
She says it's soon, very soon.

358
00:21:59,800 --> 00:22:01,120
And she is right, Wolfowitz.

359
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:02,480
Yes, beautiful, what is it?

360
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,520
Tell me.

361
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,440
He came again last night.

362
00:22:05,560 --> 00:22:06,480
- Shh.
- It's a secret?

363
00:22:06,600 --> 00:22:08,080
The Archangel.

364
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:10,880
He lay beside me and said,

365
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:14,240
"This time Adam has returned
to lead the sufferers,

366
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:17,640
"the bearers of the blue numbers,
to the desert.

367
00:22:17,760 --> 00:22:19,360
The gates of heaven will open and-"

368
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:21,000
No, of course- of course I will, Rachel.

369
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:22,840
That day is near, but not yet, dear.

370
00:22:22,960 --> 00:22:25,200
Not- not before lunch.

371
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:27,200
I will usher and proclaim and rescue.

372
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:29,120
Me, the clown?

373
00:22:35,640 --> 00:22:39,680
You see that?

374
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:43,640
You know he takes money from the patients?

375
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:46,920
Invests it in the stock market.

376
00:22:47,040 --> 00:22:48,520
Gross.

377
00:22:48,640 --> 00:22:49,600
You?

378
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:51,600
For the Institute, Slonim.

379
00:22:51,720 --> 00:22:52,960
I mean, whatever else he is,

380
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:56,480
he's a very astute financial advisor.

381
00:22:56,600 --> 00:22:59,640
You're worse than Rachel Schwester over there.

382
00:22:59,760 --> 00:23:01,280
She thinks he'll lead them all to salvation.

383
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:03,000
Adam, I need to talk to you.

384
00:23:03,120 --> 00:23:05,240
No, later, later.

385
00:23:11,240 --> 00:23:13,160
What is it?

386
00:23:13,280 --> 00:23:14,240
What is it, Adam?

387
00:23:14,360 --> 00:23:15,280
Hoof beats?

388
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,360
Gross.

389
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:25,080
Who let a dog in here?

390
00:23:37,640 --> 00:23:39,880
Nathan, who let a dog in here?

391
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:43,360
What are you talking about?

392
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:45,120
There's no dog here.

393
00:23:45,240 --> 00:23:47,760
When I first came here,

394
00:23:47,880 --> 00:23:53,480
they promised me that there would never,
ever be any dogs.

395
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,800
How could you?

396
00:23:56,920 --> 00:23:58,760
Calm down.

397
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:42,800
Edward, how are you today?

398
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:24,160
My God.

399
00:25:40,560 --> 00:25:42,400
Adam.

400
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,160
Adam.

401
00:25:52,840 --> 00:25:54,560
All right.

402
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:58,040
Come on, Adam, come on.

403
00:25:59,680 --> 00:26:02,000
Okay.

404
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:06,840
Yeah, good.

405
00:26:06,960 --> 00:26:08,480
Good.

406
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:09,560
Yeah.

407
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:26,040
Papa.

408
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:28,680
You are my angel, Ruthie.

409
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:29,760
Do not be frightened.

410
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:47,880
You.

411
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:51,400
Well, Adam Stein.

412
00:26:51,520 --> 00:26:53,720
The funniest man in Germany,

413
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:57,280
delivered to Stellring,
of all places.

414
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:01,640
Come here, Adam.

415
00:27:04,720 --> 00:27:06,040
I am Commandant Klein.

416
00:27:06,160 --> 00:27:10,680
I can't tell you how happy I am
to see you here.

417
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:13,920
You should have seen him
at the circus in Berlin.

418
00:27:14,040 --> 00:27:16,680
Any kind of animal, he could do it.

419
00:27:16,800 --> 00:27:19,080
Such a clown.

420
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:21,680
Go on, Adam.

421
00:27:21,800 --> 00:27:23,400
Do a trick.

422
00:27:25,720 --> 00:27:28,680
Make us laugh.

423
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,280
Mama, Mama.

424
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:44,400
Ruthie?

425
00:27:44,520 --> 00:27:46,440
Where are you taking me?

426
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:53,760
No, no, no.

427
00:27:53,880 --> 00:27:57,640
Now- now do a dog for Rex here.

428
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:40,840
You've made a friend, Adam.

429
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:44,160
The smell of a Jew
usually sends Rex into a frenzy.

430
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:49,000
Sergeant, take Herr Stein to Rex's pen.

431
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:50,280
No, Adam...

432
00:28:50,400 --> 00:28:51,960
on all fours.

433
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:55,640
It's funnier that way.

434
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:27,400
Go on, Adam...

435
00:29:27,520 --> 00:29:30,080
or Rex will get all the meat.

436
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:32,960
I followed your career, Adam.

437
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:36,440
You studied philosophy at Heidelberg,
didn't you?

438
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:37,560
Funny we never met there.

439
00:29:37,680 --> 00:29:39,200
Herr Kommandant, please.

440
00:29:39,320 --> 00:29:40,680
I'm a keen observer,

441
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:43,040
a student of the Semitic phenomenon.

442
00:29:43,160 --> 00:29:45,000
Of course, you're not an average specimen,

443
00:29:45,120 --> 00:29:47,360
Germany's most celebrated clown.

444
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:49,680
You're a superman, Adam,
practically Aryan.

445
00:29:49,800 --> 00:29:52,040
So maybe we can help each other.

446
00:29:52,160 --> 00:29:53,120
Head down.

447
00:29:53,240 --> 00:29:55,720
Don't look at me.

448
00:29:58,680 --> 00:30:02,200
A life for a life.

449
00:30:02,320 --> 00:30:03,280
Mine for yours.

450
00:30:03,400 --> 00:30:05,760
You stay here with me,
make me laugh,

451
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:08,720
keep my mind off the business outside.

452
00:30:08,840 --> 00:30:11,400
Believe me, it's a thankless job.

453
00:30:11,520 --> 00:30:13,160
My wife and daughters.

454
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:16,440
What's that?

455
00:30:16,560 --> 00:30:17,640
Speak up, Adam.

456
00:30:17,760 --> 00:30:19,520
My wife and daughters.

457
00:30:21,360 --> 00:30:24,160
Bargaining already, Adam.

458
00:30:24,280 --> 00:30:26,760
The Semitic phenomenon in action,

459
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:29,360
right here at my feet.

460
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:32,880
Unfortunately,
I am only Untersturmfuehrer.

461
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:34,240
I don't make the rules.

462
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:35,280
But we'll see.

463
00:30:35,400 --> 00:30:38,440
Yes, we have plenty of time.

464
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:42,000
Rex.

465
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:45,120
Go on, Adam.

466
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:52,480
Wonderful, Adam.

467
00:30:52,600 --> 00:30:53,760
Now, eat.

468
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,320
Eat.

469
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,360
Schmackhaft.

470
00:31:04,440 --> 00:31:07,320
Nothing with claws or paws.

471
00:31:07,440 --> 00:31:08,880
Seizling gave me her word.

472
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:14,200
Room 285 is in the observation ward.

473
00:31:14,320 --> 00:31:16,640
It's off-limits.

474
00:31:16,760 --> 00:31:17,800
Now, Gina tells me

475
00:31:17,920 --> 00:31:20,400
that you slept on the floor again
last night.

476
00:31:20,520 --> 00:31:22,760
Oh, is this how you're going
to break me, Gross,

477
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:24,080
with a dog?

478
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,600
Well, nice try.

479
00:31:25,720 --> 00:31:26,760
But look at me.

480
00:31:26,880 --> 00:31:28,400
See?
I'm smiling.

481
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:32,720
No, actually, Adam, you're crying.

482
00:31:32,840 --> 00:31:37,560
It is-
Yeah, you momzer- water.

483
00:31:37,680 --> 00:31:39,680
I had a- I had a drink of water
on the way.

484
00:31:39,800 --> 00:31:40,960
Through your eyes?

485
00:31:41,080 --> 00:31:43,120
Come on, Adam,
you can do better than that.

486
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:45,080
Okay, I am ready for you,
Frankenstein.

487
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:50,400
If experiments are your game,
then let's play.

488
00:31:50,520 --> 00:31:51,440
Give me your best shot.

489
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:55,080
But before you cure me,

490
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:57,400
you will all go crazy yourselves.

491
00:31:59,400 --> 00:32:01,680
The door to 285 is locked.

492
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:15,720
I'm glad to see you feeling better, Adam,

493
00:32:15,840 --> 00:32:17,120
but we're a little busy at the moment.

494
00:32:19,840 --> 00:32:21,400
Not now.

495
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:30,040
You and I, my darling,
we're going to cry together,

496
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:32,480
and I'm going to drink your tears.

497
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,080
Yes, I love very deeply.

498
00:32:34,200 --> 00:32:36,000
It is the romance supreme.

499
00:32:36,120 --> 00:32:38,760
Do you understand, my- my dar-

500
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:40,520
There are rules, Adam.

501
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:42,000
Compassion.

502
00:32:42,120 --> 00:32:43,040
Mercy.

503
00:32:43,160 --> 00:32:44,120
You're the nurse.

504
00:32:44,240 --> 00:32:45,160
What- what happened to-

505
00:32:45,280 --> 00:32:48,760
You break the tiniest rule,
you break the entire system.

506
00:32:48,880 --> 00:32:51,040
Do you know who is also
a great believer in the rules?

507
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,320
Hmm?

508
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:53,920
Kommandant Klein.

509
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:55,240
Ow.

510
00:32:55,360 --> 00:32:58,880
What a terrible thing to say.

511
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:04,960
Yeah, well, I only insult people I love.

512
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:06,040
You don't love me.

513
00:33:06,160 --> 00:33:08,000
You treat me like a dog.

514
00:33:08,120 --> 00:33:09,360
Yeah, exactly.

515
00:33:09,480 --> 00:33:10,720
Oh, but you're so wrong.

516
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:13,080
With you, I lose control.

517
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,640
When I was strangling the landlady,

518
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:16,600
who do you think
I was really strangling, Gina?

519
00:33:16,720 --> 00:33:17,640
You.

520
00:33:17,760 --> 00:33:18,960
You bastard.

521
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,000
Do it.

522
00:33:20,120 --> 00:33:21,440
Do it like I taught you, sweetheart.

523
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:24,800
No, they'll hear me.

524
00:33:24,920 --> 00:33:27,760
Do it.

525
00:33:31,000 --> 00:33:33,760
Yeah, down on your knees and crawl.

526
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:34,840
That is correct.

527
00:33:44,120 --> 00:33:46,240
Yeah, but that sounds like a schnauzer.

528
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,360
I want the wolfhound.

529
00:33:56,960 --> 00:33:57,920
Oh, I like it.

530
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:05,920
Oh, that's right.

531
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:11,000
Oh, that's right.

532
00:34:14,840 --> 00:34:17,640
You're despicable, darling.

533
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:23,480
Just give it back when you're done.

534
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:29,440
Let me see what kind of beast
has Gross brought here.

535
00:35:29,560 --> 00:35:31,320
Let me see what you are.

536
00:35:31,440 --> 00:35:32,360
Come here.

537
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,880
Ow!

538
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,960
You know you can't be in here, Adam.

539
00:36:03,080 --> 00:36:04,000
Come on.

540
00:36:04,120 --> 00:36:05,080
Come on, let's go.

541
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:06,120
Bad dog.

542
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:07,200
Bad dog.

543
00:36:07,320 --> 00:36:08,560
Bad dog.

544
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,480
Okay, let me see your hand.

545
00:36:10,600 --> 00:36:13,800
I told it I'd be back,
and it understood.

546
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,000
Get back in there.

547
00:36:18,160 --> 00:36:20,280
The stench.

548
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:22,520
Lying in his own goddamn feces.

549
00:36:22,640 --> 00:36:26,320
But the attendant,
that flea-bitten gibbon,

550
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:28,040
he did not.

551
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:29,200
Adam, stop.

