sheer unadulterated poetry.

1095
01:04:19,800 --> 01:04:21,080
Blumers, Mrs. Lipowitz.

1096
01:04:21,200 --> 01:04:24,000
Stop by my- Adam's circus

1097
01:04:24,120 --> 01:04:28,480
and see the miraculous offspring
of Olivetti und Rex.

1098
01:04:28,600 --> 01:04:29,520
Heel.

1099
01:04:29,640 --> 01:04:30,560
Heel, come on, let's go.

1100
01:04:30,680 --> 01:04:32,160
Adam.

1101
01:04:32,280 --> 01:04:33,760
No, no, no, heel, heel.

1102
01:04:33,880 --> 01:04:35,360
Come on. Come on.

1103
01:04:35,480 --> 01:04:39,040
David.

1104
01:04:39,160 --> 01:04:43,520
Wait, Adam, me first.

1105
01:04:43,640 --> 01:04:48,000
We were in Mrs. Marshack's basement.

1106
01:04:48,120 --> 01:04:53,320
13 months she was down there, Adam.

1107
01:04:53,440 --> 01:04:56,600
How much is that in numbers?

1108
01:04:56,720 --> 01:04:59,520
13 months is, um-

1109
01:04:59,640 --> 01:05:04,640
Well, it's 390 days, 9,360 hours.

1110
01:05:04,760 --> 01:05:11,760
561,600 minutes she sat there...

1111
01:05:11,880 --> 01:05:14,560
waiting.

1112
01:05:14,680 --> 01:05:16,160
Why, God?

1113
01:05:16,280 --> 01:05:17,240
Why?

1114
01:05:19,480 --> 01:05:24,560
"May his question soon be answered.

1115
01:05:24,680 --> 01:05:29,000
Signed, Abe Wolfowitz."

1116
01:05:29,120 --> 01:05:30,880
Then you say Kaddish, Adam,

1117
01:05:31,000 --> 01:05:34,320
and maybe serve some refreshments.

1118
01:05:38,080 --> 01:05:40,640
You lived, right?

1119
01:05:40,760 --> 01:05:41,760
That's what matters.

1120
01:05:41,880 --> 01:05:43,720
Yeah, yeah.

1121
01:05:43,840 --> 01:05:46,680
The circus is here?

1122
01:05:48,040 --> 01:05:49,400
Yes, it sure is, come on.

1123
01:05:49,520 --> 01:05:51,280
Come on, look how excited Rachel is.

1124
01:05:51,400 --> 01:05:53,280
Come on, yeah, oh, everyone's come.

1125
01:05:53,400 --> 01:05:54,400
Thank you. Thank you.

1126
01:05:54,520 --> 01:05:55,440
Thank you, darling.

1127
01:05:55,560 --> 01:05:56,480
Thank you, Mr. Blum, yeah.

1128
01:05:56,600 --> 01:05:57,720
Come on, Arthur.

1129
01:05:57,840 --> 01:05:59,400
All right.

1130
01:05:59,520 --> 01:06:00,880
Thank you.

1131
01:06:01,000 --> 01:06:02,600
Do the reading outside.

1132
01:06:02,720 --> 01:06:08,040
Ah, ladies and gentlemen,
meine Damen und Herren.

1133
01:06:08,160 --> 01:06:09,120
This is your big chance.

1134
01:06:09,240 --> 01:06:10,360
Ready?

1135
01:06:13,680 --> 01:06:19,000
I give you the king of dogs,
Koenig der Hund,

1136
01:06:19,120 --> 01:06:20,720
David.

1137
01:06:24,760 --> 01:06:27,200
Bravo, bravo.

1138
01:06:40,600 --> 01:06:42,720
Messages from Davey.

1139
01:06:47,400 --> 01:06:48,360
For you.

1140
01:06:49,600 --> 01:06:50,560
What?

1141
01:06:50,680 --> 01:06:51,840
What?

1142
01:06:51,960 --> 01:06:55,800
- What he is doing?
- "AT&T up 300 points."

1143
01:06:55,920 --> 01:06:57,920
Bravo, Adam.

1144
01:06:59,640 --> 01:07:01,920
He's speaking in tongues.

1145
01:07:02,040 --> 01:07:03,800
When, Adam, when?

1146
01:07:05,880 --> 01:07:07,000
What?

1147
01:07:07,120 --> 01:07:10,560
He's been pounding out gibberish.

1148
01:07:10,680 --> 01:07:13,440
Nathan, we've been treating that boy
for two months now,

1149
01:07:13,560 --> 01:07:15,520
making our way through his defenses,

1150
01:07:15,640 --> 01:07:18,240
and along comes Adam Stein
with a typewriter,

1151
01:07:18,360 --> 01:07:20,520
and you're beaming at me
like you've invented penicillin.

1152
01:07:20,640 --> 01:07:22,440
Well, I'm sure Adam
will be more than delighted

1153
01:07:22,560 --> 01:07:23,520
to share the credit.

1154
01:07:23,640 --> 01:07:24,920
Nathan, please.

1155
01:07:25,040 --> 01:07:27,360
Adam is unstable.

1156
01:07:27,480 --> 01:07:29,040
He's dangerous.

1157
01:07:29,160 --> 01:07:32,040
Instead of restricting him,
increasing his medication,

1158
01:07:32,160 --> 01:07:34,720
you give him unlimited access
to the Institute.

1159
01:07:34,840 --> 01:07:36,960
You turn a blind eye to his alcohol,

1160
01:07:37,080 --> 01:07:38,720
his love affair with your head nurse.

1161
01:07:38,840 --> 01:07:41,400
Read.

1162
01:07:41,520 --> 01:07:42,640
What do you mean, read?

1163
01:07:42,760 --> 01:07:46,160
Leave Adam to me.

1164
01:07:46,280 --> 01:07:48,560
"Gina Grey's classy ass."

1165
01:07:52,240 --> 01:07:54,880
You know what?

1166
01:07:55,000 --> 01:07:57,600
Why don't we just let the patients
cure each other,

1167
01:07:57,720 --> 01:08:01,240
and you and I can sit around
in our pajamas playing cards?

1168
01:08:01,360 --> 01:08:05,240
That is the most sensible thing
you've ever said.

1169
01:08:07,920 --> 01:08:10,240
Oh, fine, fine, fine.

1170
01:08:10,360 --> 01:08:11,360
That is my boy, David.

1171
01:08:11,480 --> 01:08:13,680
This is my king of dogs.

1172
01:08:13,800 --> 01:08:15,880
Do not eat the-
do not eat the paper.

1173
01:08:16,000 --> 01:08:19,040
Ow.

1174
01:08:19,160 --> 01:08:20,560
Stop this.

1175
01:08:20,680 --> 01:08:22,520
You are not a dog.

1176
01:08:22,640 --> 01:08:24,800
Do you know why I came back?

1177
01:08:24,920 --> 01:08:28,280
I could have died, kid, yeah.

1178
01:08:28,400 --> 01:08:30,320
The heart was blocked.

1179
01:08:30,440 --> 01:08:32,960
Slonim was pounding my chest,
calling my name.

1180
01:08:33,080 --> 01:08:34,400
There was nothing else he could do.

1181
01:08:34,520 --> 01:08:36,120
And I was wrestling with the Angel of Death.

1182
01:08:36,240 --> 01:08:37,720
I stopped him at the gate.

1183
01:08:37,840 --> 01:08:39,160
Do you know why?

1184
01:08:39,280 --> 01:08:40,600
Huh?

1185
01:08:42,480 --> 01:08:44,600
To see you again.

1186
01:08:48,160 --> 01:08:51,040
That is why.

1187
01:08:51,160 --> 01:08:52,800
I love you, child.

1188
01:08:52,920 --> 01:08:54,000
But it's no damn good.

1189
01:08:54,120 --> 01:08:58,400
You lean on me,
we will both go tumbling down together.

1190
01:09:20,920 --> 01:09:23,200
Zyklot 17.

1191
01:09:23,320 --> 01:09:25,720
Rex would have preferred it that way,
don't you think?

1192
01:09:25,840 --> 01:09:28,880
When the Russians arrive,
they will shoot him like a dog.

1193
01:09:29,000 --> 01:09:29,920
Get up.

1194
01:09:30,040 --> 01:09:32,520
I have something to show you.

1195
01:09:35,680 --> 01:09:37,720
Baron Von Hamdung.

1196
01:09:37,840 --> 01:09:39,040
Do you know the name?

1197
01:09:39,160 --> 01:09:41,960
Iron industry, shipping, petroleum.

1198
01:09:42,080 --> 01:09:43,880
Not long after the war broke out,

1199
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:46,400
he was accused of treason.

1200
01:09:46,520 --> 01:09:47,680
His entire estate,

1201
01:09:47,800 --> 01:09:52,160
Swiss bank accounts, holdings,
were nationalized.

1202
01:09:52,280 --> 01:09:57,120
A clever SS accountant-

1203
01:09:57,240 --> 01:09:58,920
well, I thought I was clever
at the time-

1204
01:09:59,040 --> 01:10:00,480
was put in charge.

1205
01:10:00,600 --> 01:10:02,200
He was meticulous,

1206
01:10:02,320 --> 01:10:04,360
which is how he rose so fast
through the ranks.

1207
01:10:04,480 --> 01:10:08,280
But this one file, he put aside.

1208
01:10:08,400 --> 01:10:11,000
In fact, he stole it.

1209
01:10:11,120 --> 01:10:14,880
And incredibly, it was never missed.

1210
01:10:17,040 --> 01:10:19,760
Patton's Third Army has crossed the Danube.

1211
01:10:19,880 --> 01:10:23,040
The Russians are in Berlin.

1212
01:10:23,160 --> 01:10:25,480
It's the end.

1213
01:10:25,600 --> 01:10:28,080
For me, this document is useless.

1214
01:10:28,200 --> 01:10:31,840
But we had a deal, you and I.

1215
01:10:31,960 --> 01:10:35,520
A life for a life.

1216
01:10:35,640 --> 01:10:36,880
So here.

1217
01:10:37,000 --> 01:10:38,800
It's Von Hamdung's last will,

1218
01:10:38,920 --> 01:10:40,960
the rights to his home and possessions,

1219
01:10:41,080 --> 01:10:46,320
and you are the sole beneficiary.

1220
01:10:46,440 --> 01:10:49,120
You've been a good dog.

1221
01:11:01,080 --> 01:11:04,360
The truth is,
I could have saved your family,

1222
01:11:04,480 --> 01:11:06,520
but it would have been inconvenient.

1223
01:11:06,640 --> 01:11:10,400
I would have had some explaining to do.

1224
01:11:10,520 --> 01:11:12,920
Do it.

1225
01:11:34,520 --> 01:11:37,840
So there's life
in the old clown yet, eh, Adam?

1226
01:12:19,560 --> 01:12:23,320
Yeah, yeah, I get it.

1227
01:12:27,840 --> 01:12:29,880
Adam Stein is at home?

1228
01:12:43,440 --> 01:12:47,400
Herr, Hermann Lichtenstein.

1229
01:12:47,520 --> 01:12:49,240
Rabbi.

1230
01:12:49,360 --> 01:12:51,920
Welcome to Valhalla.

1231
01:12:52,040 --> 01:12:54,560
Adam.

1232
01:12:54,680 --> 01:12:56,120
Look at us.

1233
01:12:56,240 --> 01:12:58,080
How can it be?

1234
01:12:59,880 --> 01:13:01,000
Oh, Rabbi.

1235
01:13:01,120 --> 01:13:02,600
It is- it's only dynamite.

1236
01:13:02,720 --> 01:13:06,480
They're putting up an apartment block next door.

1237
01:13:06,600 --> 01:13:09,440
But on my land,
no resurrection will occur.

1238
01:13:09,560 --> 01:13:11,840
You have the word of Von Hamdung.

1239
01:13:11,960 --> 01:13:14,200
How did you find me?

1240
01:13:14,320 --> 01:13:17,600
The only Jew in Germany
should be hard to find?

1241
01:13:17,720 --> 01:13:21,080
You're in the papers, Adam,
the newsreels.

1242
01:13:24,320 --> 01:13:26,880
Let me ask you.

1243
01:13:27,000 --> 01:13:31,480
Your daughter, the older one, Ruthie,

1244
01:13:31,600 --> 01:13:35,320
did you ever try to locate her?

1245
01:13:35,440 --> 01:13:37,640
Such a cheerful presence, Rabbi.

1246
01:13:37,760 --> 01:13:38,920
Truly, you light up the room.

1247
01:13:39,040 --> 01:13:40,160
I'm sorry, Adam.

1248
01:13:40,280 --> 01:13:41,320
But I have to.

1249
01:13:41,440 --> 01:13:42,400
She's dead.

1250
01:13:42,520 --> 01:13:44,320
We both are.

1251
01:13:44,440 --> 01:13:45,680
What is the point?

1252
01:13:45,800 --> 01:13:48,320
But if you have to, what, know?

1253
01:13:48,440 --> 01:13:50,960
Yeah, I did.

1254
01:13:51,080 --> 01:13:54,200
For four years, I looked.

1255
01:13:54,320 --> 01:13:59,640
I put Von Hamdung's blood money
to good use, believe me.

1256
01:13:59,760 --> 01:14:02,120
Then it dawned on me, Rabbi.

1257
01:14:02,240 --> 01:14:04,080
If she was alive,

1258
01:14:04,200 --> 01:14:07,200
then it was she
who was not looking for me.

1259
01:14:07,320 --> 01:14:08,280
Adam.

1260
01:14:08,400 --> 01:14:10,400
She would be 25 this year.

1261
01:14:10,520 --> 01:14:13,880
She would have heard about the antics
of her famous father

1262
01:14:14,000 --> 01:14:19,480
who was once a dog
and is now not much of anything.

1263
01:14:19,600 --> 01:14:21,080
And who in the world could blame her

1264
01:14:21,200 --> 01:14:24,800
if she chose to be silent?

1265
01:14:24,920 --> 01:14:26,720
We survived.

1266
01:14:26,840 --> 01:14:28,600
It's not a crime.

1267
01:14:28,720 --> 01:14:32,040
A crime is to blame yourself
instead of them.

1268
01:14:32,160 --> 01:14:34,560
Now, listen to me.

1269
01:14:34,680 --> 01:14:37,400
She is alive.

1270
01:14:37,520 --> 01:14:39,320
She was in a holding camp after the war.

1271
01:14:39,440 --> 01:14:41,280
She married an Italian,

1272
01:14:41,400 --> 01:14:43,120
and last year,
they moved to Israel.

1273
01:14:43,240 --> 01:14:44,200
Heinz.

1274
01:14:44,320 --> 01:14:46,240
She lives as a Christian in Haifa.

1275
01:14:46,360 --> 01:14:47,920
We were notified three weeks ago

1276
01:14:48,040 --> 01:14:50,240
when she was admitted
to the Franciscan Hospital.

1277
01:14:50,360 --> 01:14:52,960
They looked at her papers and contacted us.

1278
01:14:53,080 --> 01:14:54,560
Hospital?

1279
01:14:54,680 --> 01:14:59,680
The Nazis, they injured her,
body and soul,

1280
01:14:59,800 --> 01:15:02,080
but she lived.

1281
01:15:02,200 --> 01:15:04,880
And now, thank God,

1282
01:15:05,000 --> 01:15:08,800
you are about to become a grandfather.

1283
01:15:08,920 --> 01:15:12,400
I think it's time to talk to her.

1284
01:15:12,520 --> 01:15:17,760
And if not to be forgiven,
then maybe at least to be heard.

1285
01:15:17,880 --> 01:15:22,560
Rabbi, you have some nerve
coming here to my sarcophagus.

1286
01:15:22,680 --> 01:15:24,760
Heinz, get my gun.

1287
01:15:28,240 --> 01:15:30,720
Her name and address,
should you so choose.

1288
01:15:30,840 --> 01:15:33,160
You don't have to punish yourself, Adam.

1289
01:15:33,280 --> 01:15:35,360
Why stay in Berlin?

1290
01:15:35,480 --> 01:15:38,280
What's keeping you here?

1291
01:15:42,560 --> 01:15:45,720
You're not dead yet, Adam.

1292
01:15:55,640 --> 01:15:56,640
It's so hot in here.

1293
01:15:56,760 --> 01:15:57,680
Why is it so hot?

1294
01:15:57,800 --> 01:15:58,840
It's a hothouse, Adam.

1295
01:15:58,960 --> 01:16:00,320
Hothouse in the desert, typical.

1296
01:16:00,440 --> 01:16:02,000
What is he growing anyway?

1297
01:16:02,120 --> 01:16:07,000
Oh, melons, tomatoes,
herbs for the kitchen.

1298
01:16:07,120 --> 01:16:08,760
Hey.

1299
01:16:08,880 --> 01:16:16,320
Today you were thinking about Gretchen.

1300
01:16:16,440 --> 01:16:17,880
Oh, no, no.

1301
01:16:18,000 --> 01:16:19,280
Lady, this is not so nice.

1302
01:16:19,400 --> 01:16:21,840
You have no right to be brooding
about Gretchen.

1303
01:16:21,960 --> 01:16:24,160
That woman had faith in me.

1304
01:16:24,280 --> 01:16:26,360
Adam clowning around
as she took her final steps,

1305
01:16:26,480 --> 01:16:27,400
and she had faith in me.

1306
01:16:27,520 --> 01:16:28,480
You have faith in no one.

1307
01:16:28,600 --> 01:16:29,600
I have faith in you.

1308
01:16:29,720 --> 01:16:32,960
You are lying.

1309
01:16:33,080 --> 01:16:35,000
Don't, please.

1310
01:16:38,680 --> 01:16:41,640
No one's been able
to get through to him but you,

1311
01:16:41,760 --> 01:16:43,160
the poor child.

1312
01:16:43,280 --> 01:16:44,200
It is not a child.

1313
01:16:44,320 --> 01:16:45,440
Do not call him the child.

1314
01:16:45,560 --> 01:16:48,600
- Dog, he's a dog.
- He types on a typewriter.

1315
01:16:48,720 --> 01:16:50,280
He doesn't bark anymore.

1316
01:16:50,400 --> 01:16:53,600
You, God, made him into a child.

1317
01:16:53,720 --> 01:16:57,800
He was non-human; now he is human.

1318
01:16:57,920 --> 01:16:59,920
Wait a minute.

1319
01:17:06,560 --> 01:17:08,040
Are you jealous?

1320
01:17:08,160 --> 01:17:10,720
Why can't I be jealous?

1321
01:17:10,840 --> 01:17:12,880
Of course I'm jealous.

1322
01:17:13,000 --> 01:17:14,680
I'm jealous of the boy.

1323
01:17:14,800 --> 01:17:16,880
I'm jealous of Gretchen.

1324
01:17:17,000 --> 01:17:21,240
We used to be together so much before.

1325
01:17:21,360 --> 01:17:22,600
I used to bark for you.

1326
01:17:22,720 --> 01:17:24,360
I can still bark.

1327
01:17:29,320 --> 01:17:31,160
You are not a-
you are not a dog.

1328
01:17:31,280 --> 01:17:32,760
Gina.

1329
01:17:32,880 --> 01:17:34,000
Bitch at heart.

1330
01:17:34,120 --> 01:17:36,600
You- stop barking.

1331
01:17:36,720 --> 01:17:38,040
Stop barking.

1332
01:17:40,760 --> 01:17:44,160
You're not going to come between us.

1333
01:17:44,280 --> 01:17:47,360
This child is mine.

1334
01:17:47,480 --> 01:17:49,840
We are two dogs in the desert.

1335
01:17:49,960 --> 01:17:53,120
I took off his mask,
and now he wants my power.

1336
01:17:53,240 --> 01:17:54,920
I cannot be the true dog.

1337
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:56,400
Neither can he.

1338
01:17:56,520 --> 01:17:58,720
He's a child.

1339
01:17:58,840 --> 01:18:00,360
He needs love.

1340
01:18:00,480 --> 01:18:03,920
You had better not interfere.

1341
01:18:14,400 --> 01:18:15,360
Keep going, kid.

1342
01:18:15,480 --> 01:18:16,440
We are going to do this.

1343
01:18:16,560 --> 01:18:17,920
Marsch, hund.

1344
01:18:18,040 --> 01:18:19,400
Come on, hey.

1345
01:18:19,520 --> 01:18:20,600
You see this fence?

1346
01:18:20,720 --> 01:18:22,040
You are going to grab onto the fence

1347
01:18:22,160 --> 01:18:23,120
and stand on your feet.

1348
01:18:23,240 --> 01:18:24,160
This is all your fault.

1349
01:18:24,280 --> 01:18:25,240
Everything I did for you,

1350
01:18:25,360 --> 01:18:26,600
and now for me,
you are going to do one thing.

1351
01:18:26,720 --> 01:18:29,280
Here we go.
Stand.

1352
01:18:29,400 --> 01:18:30,760
Oh.

1353
01:18:30,880 --> 01:18:32,000
Ah, hund, hund.

1354
01:18:32,120 --> 01:18:34,400
Come on, schnell.

1355
01:18:34,520 --> 01:18:36,560
Okay, you ever been to a circus, huh?

1356
01:18:36,680 --> 01:18:39,040
Bears, horses, lions,

1357
01:18:39,160 --> 01:18:41,520
every goddamn creature on this Earth.

1358
01:18:41,640 --> 01:18:43,840
Even Arthur Fine can stand on two feet.

1359
01:18:43,960 --> 01:18:44,880
You're not the dog.

1360
01:18:45,000 --> 01:18:45,960
You're not the boy.

1361
