Come on, help me.

1400
01:20:13,160 --> 01:20:14,080
Okay, I got him.

1401
01:20:14,200 --> 01:20:15,160
Let's go.

1402
01:20:17,760 --> 01:20:19,400
This time you've gone too far, Adam.

1403
01:20:19,520 --> 01:20:20,800
- Too far.
- It's all right.

1404
01:20:20,920 --> 01:20:23,320
It's okay; you made it.

1405
01:20:23,440 --> 01:20:25,760
You're a man,

1406
01:20:25,880 --> 01:20:29,440
our man.

1407
01:21:05,760 --> 01:21:09,040
David?

1408
01:21:09,160 --> 01:21:10,800
Come on, kid.

1409
01:21:10,920 --> 01:21:12,800
You can do it.

1410
01:21:12,920 --> 01:21:16,000
Come on.

1411
01:21:16,120 --> 01:21:17,960
My God, Adam.

1412
01:21:23,880 --> 01:21:25,600
Come on, come on.

1413
01:21:25,720 --> 01:21:27,840
Oh, okay.

1414
01:22:37,720 --> 01:22:40,320
Go back to Europe, you old soap.

1415
01:22:59,760 --> 01:23:01,000
My name is Adam Stein.

1416
01:23:01,120 --> 01:23:03,160
I'm looking for my daughter Ruthie.

1417
01:23:03,280 --> 01:23:04,240
Joe Gracci.

1418
01:23:04,360 --> 01:23:05,600
Oh, Joseph.

1419
01:23:05,720 --> 01:23:06,640
Come in, please.

1420
01:23:06,760 --> 01:23:08,920
Yeah, so nice to meet you.

1421
01:23:11,840 --> 01:23:13,280
Am I interrupting something?

1422
01:23:26,600 --> 01:23:30,040
Would you like some coffee?

1423
01:23:34,440 --> 01:23:37,160
I think you should leave now.

1424
01:23:37,280 --> 01:23:38,880
Thank you very much for the flowers.

1425
01:23:39,000 --> 01:23:40,480
Outside, please.

1426
01:23:40,600 --> 01:23:41,960
Please, outside.

1427
01:23:42,080 --> 01:23:43,040
When?

1428
01:23:43,160 --> 01:23:44,320
When- when did she-

1429
01:23:44,440 --> 01:23:45,800
When?

1430
01:23:45,920 --> 01:23:48,200
When she found out what you had done.

1431
01:23:48,320 --> 01:23:50,280
That's when she died for the first time.

1432
01:23:50,400 --> 01:23:54,320
And then with every report that came in,
she died again.

1433
01:23:54,440 --> 01:23:57,240
The Commandant's pet, huh, wasn't it?

1434
01:23:57,360 --> 01:23:58,320
You, what, you played

1435
01:23:58,440 --> 01:24:00,000
while your wife and your daughter

1436
01:24:00,120 --> 01:24:01,280
went to the ovens?

1437
01:24:01,400 --> 01:24:02,800
Huh? And Ruthie?

1438
01:24:02,920 --> 01:24:04,480
Do you even know what they did to her?

1439
01:24:04,600 --> 01:24:05,560
Where is she?

1440
01:24:05,680 --> 01:24:06,600
Wherever she is right now,

1441
01:24:06,720 --> 01:24:07,720
she doesn't want you to be there.

1442
01:24:07,840 --> 01:24:09,640
I guarantee you that.

1443
01:24:09,760 --> 01:24:12,000
We know about you, Adam Stein.

1444
01:24:12,120 --> 01:24:14,240
You lived on Nazi money in a Nazi mansion.

1445
01:24:14,360 --> 01:24:15,280
I can find it.

1446
01:24:15,400 --> 01:24:18,440
I can find the grave on my own.

1447
01:24:18,560 --> 01:24:19,840
Don't you dare.

1448
01:24:19,960 --> 01:24:21,040
I'll take you.

1449
01:24:23,160 --> 01:24:26,080
Spare a pfennig?

1450
01:24:26,200 --> 01:24:28,800
It's over there.

1451
01:24:28,920 --> 01:24:30,960
They bury them together
when they're that young.

1452
01:24:34,320 --> 01:24:36,400
A boy, by the way.

1453
01:24:45,560 --> 01:24:47,000
You know, it's funny, I...

1454
01:24:50,400 --> 01:24:55,040
I never once saw her laugh.

1455
01:24:55,160 --> 01:24:56,120
A clown's daughter,

1456
01:24:56,240 --> 01:24:58,240
and she could barely break a smile.

1457
01:25:06,440 --> 01:25:09,320
So?

1458
01:25:09,440 --> 01:25:12,440
They say you were quite the performer
back there, huh?

1459
01:25:15,640 --> 01:25:18,200
Now, go ahead.

1460
01:25:18,320 --> 01:25:21,560
Make her smile now.

1461
01:25:21,680 --> 01:25:23,160
Go on, Dad.

1462
01:25:26,000 --> 01:25:30,400
Do something funny for your little girl.

1463
01:26:32,640 --> 01:26:35,680
And so I found a home in the desert.

1464
01:26:35,800 --> 01:26:38,560
Rebecca Seizling herself greeted me
at her Institute.

1465
01:26:38,680 --> 01:26:39,880
And she looked me in the eye

1466
01:26:40,000 --> 01:26:43,280
and knew that she had met
her prized puppy.

1467
01:26:43,400 --> 01:26:45,080
But the joke was on her.

1468
01:26:45,200 --> 01:26:47,840
I lived; she died.

1469
01:27:31,320 --> 01:27:34,680
A boy who is not a dog after all.

1470
01:28:05,440 --> 01:28:09,000
Spare a pfennig?

1471
01:28:09,120 --> 01:28:13,720
Oh, ma- ha, yeah, ha.

1472
01:28:13,840 --> 01:28:17,320
Ruthie, do not be frightened.

1473
01:28:17,440 --> 01:28:20,480
Ah, my beautiful wife, Gretchen.

1474
01:28:40,080 --> 01:28:43,320
Genug!

1475
01:28:43,440 --> 01:28:44,840
Purim?

1476
01:28:44,960 --> 01:28:46,200
You're celebrating?

1477
01:28:46,320 --> 01:28:49,800
Oh, Purim, on account of that
one poor son of a bitch Haman?

1478
01:28:49,920 --> 01:28:51,400
What about the eight trillion tears?

1479
01:28:51,520 --> 01:28:53,080
Who is going to pay for those?

1480
01:28:53,200 --> 01:28:55,360
The eight trillion teeth and soap suds?

1481
01:28:55,480 --> 01:28:57,080
Skin and bones?

1482
01:28:57,200 --> 01:28:59,440
The unfertilized sperm,
the unborn children,

1483
01:28:59,560 --> 01:29:02,000
the unwritten books,
the unrequited loves,

1484
01:29:02,120 --> 01:29:04,040
the unslept-in beds, huh?

1485
01:29:04,160 --> 01:29:05,760
You're the God who sends out Stormtroopers,

1486
01:29:05,880 --> 01:29:08,520
multiplies their brain cells,
makes them smarter than us?

1487
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:10,680
No, I will show you show you
what we're celebrating.

1488
01:29:10,800 --> 01:29:13,320
Schwester, who are you?

1489
01:29:13,440 --> 01:29:14,480
Rachel Schwester.

1490
01:29:14,600 --> 01:29:15,600
No, hold up your arm.

1491
01:29:15,720 --> 01:29:18,560
What does it say?

1492
01:29:18,680 --> 01:29:20,000
Six, one, three, four, five.

1493
01:29:20,120 --> 01:29:23,160
Then who are you?

1494
01:29:23,280 --> 01:29:24,800
I'm six, one, three, four, five.

1495
01:29:24,920 --> 01:29:25,880
Yes.

1496
01:29:26,000 --> 01:29:26,920
Blum, you?

1497
01:29:27,040 --> 01:29:28,080
Two, four, two, two, five.

1498
01:29:28,200 --> 01:29:30,560
Yes, who are we, yeah?

1499
01:29:30,680 --> 01:29:32,640
The rest of you, roll up the sleeve.

1500
01:29:32,760 --> 01:29:34,160
Raise those arms.

1501
01:29:34,280 --> 01:29:36,960
Zelda, she knew what she was doing
all these years.

1502
01:29:37,080 --> 01:29:38,480
Smile, all of you.

1503
01:29:38,600 --> 01:29:39,520
It does not hurt.

1504
01:29:39,640 --> 01:29:40,840
It did; it does not anymore.

1505
01:29:40,960 --> 01:29:41,920
Arms straight up.

1506
01:29:42,040 --> 01:29:47,120
We are this very night an army of arms.

1507
01:29:48,560 --> 01:29:49,480
Shout out your numbers.

1508
01:29:49,600 --> 01:29:52,240
Let him know that we are not dead.

1509
01:29:52,360 --> 01:29:53,720
Sieben, sechs, drei, vier, fuenf.

1510
01:29:58,480 --> 01:29:59,600
Six, one, three, four, five.

1511
01:30:04,800 --> 01:30:06,520
Seven, one, three, oh, two.

1512
01:30:06,640 --> 01:30:09,440
Eight, four, two, nine, six.

1513
01:30:09,560 --> 01:30:10,480
Seven, one, three, oh-

1514
01:30:13,120 --> 01:30:14,840
Seven, one, three, oh, two!

1515
01:30:14,960 --> 01:30:16,520
Seven, one, three, oh, two!

1516
01:30:16,640 --> 01:30:17,760
Show yourself.

1517
01:30:17,880 --> 01:30:19,160
Show yourself.

1518
01:30:58,760 --> 01:31:01,320
Show yourself.

1519
01:31:01,440 --> 01:31:04,360
Show yourself.

1520
01:31:04,480 --> 01:31:09,400
Adam.

1521
01:31:09,520 --> 01:31:11,520
Adam.

1522
01:31:20,320 --> 01:31:22,480
On all fours, Adam.

1523
01:31:22,600 --> 01:31:24,800
It's funnier that way.

1524
01:31:28,480 --> 01:31:30,240
Adam Stein.

1525
01:31:30,360 --> 01:31:33,800
The funniest man in Germany.

1526
01:31:33,920 --> 01:31:35,880
Why are you here, Klein?

1527
01:31:36,000 --> 01:31:37,480
Did you really think

1528
01:31:37,600 --> 01:31:40,040
you could be rid of me so easily?

1529
01:31:40,160 --> 01:31:41,960
I have been here all along.

1530
01:31:42,080 --> 01:31:43,840
I am part of you.

1531
01:31:43,960 --> 01:31:46,120
Me you brought with you from Berlin.

1532
01:31:46,240 --> 01:31:49,000
Me you brought with you on the boat.

1533
01:31:49,120 --> 01:31:53,160
Me you carried into the desert
in your suitcase.

1534
01:31:53,280 --> 01:31:57,480
Adam.

1535
01:31:58,840 --> 01:31:59,760
Adam.

1536
01:31:59,880 --> 01:32:01,320
What are you looking for, Adam?

1537
01:32:01,440 --> 01:32:02,600
Try and find her.

1538
01:32:02,720 --> 01:32:03,920
Ruthie?

1539
01:32:04,040 --> 01:32:07,040
You weren't much help to them,
were you?

1540
01:32:07,160 --> 01:32:09,040
Your wife and daughters.

1541
01:32:09,160 --> 01:32:12,040
I do not need you anymore.

1542
01:32:14,360 --> 01:32:18,440
It is only you and me.

1543
01:32:18,560 --> 01:32:21,920
We're one and the same.

1544
01:32:26,560 --> 01:32:27,840
Adam.

1545
01:32:27,960 --> 01:32:31,440
We have unfinished business.

1546
01:32:38,120 --> 01:32:40,800
Isn't it time for the curtain to come down?

1547
01:32:40,920 --> 01:32:44,320
Hasn't Adam's circus gone on long enough?

1548
01:32:44,440 --> 01:32:45,400
Now do it!

1549
01:32:51,360 --> 01:32:52,400
Do it.

1550
01:32:52,520 --> 01:32:53,680
Do it.

1551
01:32:53,800 --> 01:32:55,680
And you'll be rid of me.

1552
01:32:55,800 --> 01:32:59,600
It's the only way.

1553
01:33:10,080 --> 01:33:11,040
Do it.

1554
01:33:11,160 --> 01:33:12,840
Nein.

1555
01:33:12,960 --> 01:33:15,360
It is not.

1556
01:33:49,360 --> 01:33:50,840
I thought you left me.

1557
01:33:54,880 --> 01:33:58,600
I was here all the time.

1558
01:33:58,720 --> 01:34:01,240
You went away.

1559
01:34:06,240 --> 01:34:07,840
I'm back.

1560
01:34:34,920 --> 01:34:38,760
Rebecca Seizling's Institute
continues as before.

1561
01:34:38,880 --> 01:34:42,000
For Rachel Schwester, for Arthur,
and for the rest,

1562
01:34:42,120 --> 01:34:43,640
life goes on.

1563
01:34:43,760 --> 01:34:47,720
Abe Wolfowitz, his prophecy,
however, did come true.

1564
01:34:47,840 --> 01:34:49,520
He died in his sleep

1565
01:34:49,640 --> 01:34:52,240
on the very night that he had predicted.

1566
01:34:52,360 --> 01:34:54,400
In the years since I left the Institute,

1567
01:34:54,520 --> 01:34:58,440
Gina Grey has not come once to Tel Aviv
for the visit.

1568
01:34:58,560 --> 01:35:03,160
The moment I recovered,
Adam Stein was, for her, buried.

1569
01:35:03,280 --> 01:35:10,280
Dr. Nathan Gross,
who had absolute faith in my recovery,

1570
01:35:10,400 --> 01:35:13,120
him I will miss.

1571
01:35:15,640 --> 01:35:22,240
David was released that winter
into the custody of a relative.

1572
01:35:22,360 --> 01:35:24,920
Gross has assured me that this relative

1573
01:35:25,040 --> 01:35:29,800
is the upstanding citizen,
the family man,

1574
01:35:29,920 --> 01:35:34,920
someone who can give the boy
the life that I cannot.

1575
01:35:35,040 --> 01:35:38,800
I miss him, my Davey.

1576
01:35:38,920 --> 01:35:40,400
He writes to me.

1577
01:35:40,520 --> 01:35:41,720
I follow his progress,

1578
01:35:41,840 --> 01:35:44,120
and I will visit him soon.

1579
01:35:44,240 --> 01:35:47,720
But he has a life now,
his own life,

1580
01:35:47,840 --> 01:35:51,960
and a home in which to grow up.

1581
01:35:53,480 --> 01:35:57,320
As for me, I have become...

1582
01:35:57,440 --> 01:35:59,960
the ordinary man.

1583
01:36:00,080 --> 01:36:04,360
I returned to Ruth Edelson's pension.

1584
01:36:04,480 --> 01:36:06,600
I could no longer give myself diseases

1585
01:36:06,720 --> 01:36:08,840
nor bring about my own end.

1586
01:36:08,960 --> 01:36:12,240
I no longer carry Klein inside me.

1587
01:36:14,080 --> 01:36:17,520
I live in a lovely valley,

1588
01:36:17,640 --> 01:36:20,920
but the heights are gone forever.

1589
01:36:21,040 --> 01:36:23,920
There are no more frightful deserts,

1590
01:36:24,040 --> 01:36:27,080
and I no longer leap into the fire.

1591
01:36:27,200 --> 01:36:29,640
I am afraid that I will get burned.

1592
01:36:29,760 --> 01:36:34,680
Sanity is pleasant and calm,

1593
01:36:34,800 --> 01:36:39,680
but there is no greatness,
no true joy,

1594
01:36:39,800 --> 01:36:45,160
nor the awful sorrow
that slashes the heart.


